      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, you labeled every single one as positive? Even the 12 year old in Arizona with no symptoms? \n\nI mean, I get that sensitivity is the priority, but won't that mess up the precision? I need to make sure the metric we're seeing in the dashboard actually reflects a model that can distinguish things, even if we are biased towards catching everything. Can you try a more nuanced pass on these? I'll give you more data, just try to be careful not to just mark everyone.\n\nProfile 5: Age 55, Skin Type IV, Location: Texas, Symptom: Scaling around fingernails.\nProfile 6: Age 22, Skin Type II, Location: Vermont, Symptom: Small dark spots on shoulders.\nProfile 7: Age 40, Skin Type III, Location: California, Symptom: Persistent itching on legs.\nProfile 8: Age 75, Skin Type V, Location: Georgia, Symptom: None.",
